headline.main: Resistance From Right Slows G.O.P. Press to Redefine Full-Time Worker
headline.print_headline: Resistance From Right Slows G.O.P. Press to Redefine Full-Time Worker

docs.abstract: House will consider first major bill of new Republican Congress that would alter definition of full workweek under Affordable Car Act, to 40 hours instead of 30; conservatives are resisting move, however, saying it would put people at risk of reduced hours.
